    CuramTimeConverter

    public class SvrDateTimeConverter
extends DateTimeConverter

    A converter for the SVR_DATETIME domain. The format of the date and time are defined by the application's date format and time format. The generic format complies with the ISO 8601 standard formats. The generic parser accepts several ISO 8601 formats, but the generic formatter will always output the full "yyyyMMddTHHmmss" format. The system "zero" date-time is formatted as an empty string.

    This converter uses the system's default time zone when converting values. If the active user's preferred time zone should be applied, use the DateTimeConverter plug-in class instead.

      • getTimeZone

        public java.util.TimeZone getTimeZone()
        Gets the time zone associated with this plug-in instance. The time zone is typically derived from the active time zone of the user who made the request that triggered the processing that required this plug-in. This implementation overrides the active user's time zone and returns the system's default time zone instead. This provides compatibility with the old behavior of date-time conversion after the introduction of new, user-specific time zone support in the DateTimeConverter plug-in. The new plug-in has replaced this plug-in in the default domain plug-in configuration.
        Specified by:
        getTimeZone in interface PlugIn
        Overrides:

        Returns:
        The time zone. May be null.
